productDetails.description:
ZIONOR G5 series swimming goggles are made of high quality latex-free, non-toxic and odorless silicone material. Featured with Anti-fog, shock-resistant, 100% UV protection and a durable TPR nose bridge.

How to replace nose bridges on ZIONOR G5 swim goggles?

The nose bridge attached with the lenses by four little "feet", thus you need to remove them one by one.
1. Pull out one "foot" from the hole, say bottom one on the right lens.
2. Twist the right lens and nose bridge in opposite way a little bit and pull out the other "foot" on the right.
3. Do the same thing on the left.
4. Install the nose bridges from one side to the other. Make sure four "feet" stand in the holes correctly.
You can also search "how to change nose bridges of ZIONOR G5" on Youtube for more details.

operating steps:

When using semi-automatic mode, just simply plug in the pump, leave power switch to "off" position and press the nozzle to inflate. If stop pressing, inflation will stop as well.

productDetails.description:
Q: Why is my yoga ball smaller than expected?
A: Please refer to the inflation instructions. After the initial inflation, let the ball sit undisturbed for 48 hours, and then inflate it again to achieve the desired size. This process allows the material to adjust and the ball to expand fully.
Q: What does it mean that the fitness ball is "ANTI-BURST"?
A: "Anti-burst" means that when the fitness ball is subjected to weight, even if pierced by a sharp object around the size of 1*4mm, it will slowly deflate instead of bursting suddenly. This design is intended to prevent injuries during use. All Trideer yoga balls undergo thorough limit load tests before leaving the factory, ensuring they can withstand weights of up to 330 lbs.
Q: How do I choose the right size for a yoga ball?
A: To select the appropriate size for a yoga ball, consider your height. Trideer offers a variety of options. Generally, the Small (S) size is suitable for individuals below 4'5", the Medium (M) size for heights between 4'5''-5'1'', the Large (L) size for those between 5'1''-5'9", and the Extra Large (XL) size for heights between 5'9''-6'3''. The XL size is suitable for individuals 6'3'' and above. Choosing the right size ensures proper alignment and effectiveness during exercises.

productDetails.description:
Outdoor enthusiasts know that when the going gets tough, so should their insect repellent. However extreme the activity or terrain, there's a Repel insect repellent designed to offer dependable coverage that lasts as long as you need it to. Repel products make effective mosquito protection simple under any circumstance—so you can heed the call of the wild wherever the trail takes you.

Repel 100 Insect Repellent provides you with up to 10 hours of protection. Spending a long time outdoors can be refreshing, but mosquitoes can bring that to a halt. This convenient 1 ounce travel-size pump spray can be easily stored with whatever gear your adventure requires. Formulated for severe insect conditions, Repel 100 Insect Repellent contains 98.11% DEET. Repel mosquitoes that may transmit the Zika, West Nile, Dengue and Chikungunya viruses, as well as ticks, gnats, biting flies, chiggers and fleas. Extreme conditions call for strong protection. Make Repel 100 Insect Repellent your bug spray essential.

DEET has been used as an insect repellent in the United States for more than 50 years. It’s recommended for those spending longer periods of time outdoors, in more heavily infested conditions. Recommended by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention for effective, long-lasting protection against mosquitoes, DEET is also an effective repellent for ticks. DEET-based products are available in a wide variety of Repel formulas, including aerosols, sprays and wipes.
